      "title": "<span id=\"#11948\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">greedy</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>古英语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">grædig</span>（西撒克逊）， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gredig</span>（安格鲁）“贪婪的，饥饿的”，也指“贪婪的，渴望获得的”，源自原始日耳曼语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*grædagaz</span>（源头还包括古撒克逊语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gradag</span> “贪婪的”，古诺尔斯语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">graðr</span> “贪婪，饥饿”，丹麦语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">graadig</span>，荷兰语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gretig</span>，古高地德语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gratag</span> “贪婪的”，哥特语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gredags</span> “饥饿的”），源自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*græduz</span>（源头还包括哥特语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gredus</span> “饥饿”，古英语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">grædum</span> “渴望”），可能源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*gher-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *gher- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*gher-</a>（2）“喜欢，想要”（梵语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">grdh</span> “贪婪”源头）。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins><p>在希腊语中，这个词是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">philargyros</i>，字面意思是“爱钱的”。德语中的一个词是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">habsüchtig</i>，源自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">haben</i> “拥有”+ <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sucht</i> “疾病，疾病”，意思倾向于“热情”。</p>"
    }
  ],
